The paper proposes a new approach to designing convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification and semantic segmentation tasks. As such, it is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science on arXiv. 

Firstly, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category, as the paper focuses on image-related tasks and proposes a new architecture for CNNs. 

Secondly, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely, as the paper proposes a new approach to learning the optimal architecture for a given task, which is a key challenge in machine learning. 

Thirdly, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible sub-category, as the paper proposes a new approach to designing neural networks that could have broader implications for AI research. 

Fourthly, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category, as the paper proposes a new type of neural network architecture that embeds an exponentially large number of architectures. 

Finally, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible, as the paper proposes a new approach to semantic segmentation, which involves understanding the meaning of language in images.
